{"questionId":"32941116","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The dog food is sold in closed cylindrical containers, with radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> and height <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/5c5bd7ac1c1dc43ad9876053818b1531174865c0.png\"></p>\n<p>The whole container is made from one type of material, and it is assumed that the thickness of the material is negligible.</p>\n<p>Each container has a volume of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>400</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down an equation, in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math>, that shows this information.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>400</mn><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>h</mi></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32941116","referenceCode":"24N.2.SL.TZ1.4c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down an equation, in terms of r and h, that shows this information.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Prior learning"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}